## `dwm-flexipatch`

<https://github.com/bakkeby/dwm-flexipatch>

## Patches Used

`COOL_AUTOSTART_PATCH`

:   I used to put my commands inside `.xprofile` or `.xinitrc` but I had issues with this method. for example when I tried the `ly` display manager it read the `.xprofile` file. while when using `startx` it read `.xinitrc`. I think auto starting programs can be simplified in a unified method. I think the window manager should be responsible for starting programs. This is why I use this patch.

`MOVESTACK_PATCH`

:   It lets us move windows in the stacked area. By default you can only swap windows between stacked and master areas.

`PERTAG_PATCH`

:   Normally when you increase or decrease master size on one workspace (tag), it applies globally on all tags. This is annoying. With this patch all tags have their own master and stack area sizes

`PERTAG_VANITYGAPS_PATCH`

:   Same thing for gaps. I want my gaps on tag 3 but not in tag 1. this patch does that.

`SCRATCHPADS_PATCH`

:   A big game changer. A floating terminal you can toggle on every tag. For quick typing, quick calculation for example or python interpreter etc. You can even use `tmux` in that terminal so you have named scratchpads in one place

`BAR_PADDING_SMART_PATCH`

:   Disable window borders when there is only one window in the workspace

`FOCUSADJACENTTAG_PATCH`

:   I use `Alt+l` and `Alt+h` to quickly navigate tags on the left and rights. This patch allows it

`SPAWNCMD_PATCH`

:   keep working directory of currently focused terminal when launching a new terminal

`STICKY_PATCH`

:   make a floating window sticky using `Alt+s`

`SENDMON_KEEPFOCUS_PATCH`
:   keep focus on the current monitor when sending one of the window to another monitor

## Enable Patches

`cd` into `dwm-flexipatch` and open up `patches.def.h` file. Now activate patches just by putting `1` in front of the target patch

## Process

``` {.bash org-language="sh"}
cd ~/project/repos/tools/suckless
git clone https://github.com/bakkeby/dwm-flexipatch.git
```

## Integrate dwm-flexipatch in configuration.nix

Since `dwm-flexipatch` is not a nix package, we need to custom build it. Here we create a derivation of dwm. we put this `let` block on top of our `configuration.nix`

``` nix
let
  dwmFlexipatch = pkgs.stdenv.mkDerivation {
    pname = "dwm-flexipatch";
    version = "6.8";

    src = builtins.path {
      path = /home/savolla/project/repos/one-ring/tools/suckless/dwm-flexipatch;
      name = "dwm-flexipatch-src";
    };

    nativeBuildInputs = [ pkgs.gnumake pkgs.gcc pkgs.pkg-config ];
    buildInputs = [ pkgs.libx11 pkgs.libxft pkgs.libxinerama pkgs.libxrandr pkgs.libxcursor ];
    installPhase = ''
      mkdir -p $out/bin
      rm config.h patches.h
      make clean
      make
      cp dwm $out/bin/
    '';
  };
in
```

Then let\'s add this derivation in our system packages

``` nix
systemPackages = with pkgs; [
  dwmFlexipatch
];
```

Finally use this package as dwm package instead of default one like this;

``` nix
services = {
  xserver = {
    enable = true;
    windowManager = {
      dwm = {
        enable = true;
        package = dwmFlexipatch;
      };
    };
  };
};
```

